description:
&lt;p&gt;This post is for a Neurology Teaching Fellow based at the Manchester Centre for Clinical Neurosciences, Salford Royal Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Manchester Centre for Clinical Neurosciences serves a large population and has a full complement of neurological subspecialties encompassing; Stroke, Cognitive function, Neuromuscular, Epilepsy, Neuroimmunology and Movement Disorders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post has been designed to contribute to the provision of high quality neurology services to the Greater Manchester population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate will have the opportunity to develop and gain experience in the delivery of Undergraduate Neurology Teaching whilst gaining valuable postgraduate experience in Clinical Neurosciences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a fully registered medical practitioners and hold a current GMC licence to practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have post-graduate medical experience with either current employment in a UKFPO-affiliated Foundation Programme or 12 months’ experience post-full GMC registration and evidence of achievement of foundation competencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Completion of MRCP (or equivalent) is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts benefit from the clinical supervision / educational supervision and in-house educational programme opportunities given to our training grade medical posts at SpR grade level. Support will be available to access e-portfolio and leave for certain approved educational activity / courses as deemed appropriate for the applicants’ level of training and experience. Initially a temporary post for 12 months, but with potential for extension depending on progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with the Trust’s Single Equality Scheme we welcome applications from everyone irrespective of ethnic origin, disability, age, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, nationality, religion, marital status, social back ground or trade union membership. However, as members of ethnicity minority groups and individuals with disabilities are currently under-represented at this level of post, we would encourage applications from members of these groups. Appointment will be based on merit alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Tim LavinJob titleConsultant NeurologistEmail addressTim.lavin@srft.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 206 4590&lt;/p&gt;
